tinny/tinnie
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a small package of cannabis wrapped in tinfoil as sold by drug-vendors.
Origin: [none]
Register: informal
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Worik Stanton (worik@noggon.com)writes that his wife commented "we called them tinnies in Palmerston [North] but when I got to Auckland I found they were called foils."
